# Architecture Rules

## Module Boundaries

### UI Components (`src/components/ui/`)
- Domain-agnostic primitives only
- No knowledge of resume/analysis concepts
- Accept `className` prop for customization
- Use `cn()` for class merging

### Feature Modules (`src/features/`)
- Domain-aware components and hooks
- Co-located types, hooks, and components
- Export through index.ts barrel file
- Can import from `ui/` and `lib/`

### Server Code (`src/server/`)
- Server-only code, never import in client
- AI prompts and services
- File parsing logic
- Validation utilities

### API Routes (`src/app/api/`)
- Orchestrate server logic
- Validate requests with Zod
- Return structured JSON responses
- Handle errors gracefully

## Import Rules

```typescript
// Good: UI component imports lib utilities
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils/cn';

// Good: Feature imports UI components
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button';

// Bad: UI component imports feature code
import { useResumeUpload } from '@/features/resume-upload';

// Bad: Client code imports server code
import { parseResumeWithAi } from '@/server/ai/services';
```

## File Organization

- Keep files small and focused
- One component per file
- Co-locate related code in feature folders
- Use index.ts for public exports
